title: Speakers in Security Council Hail Efforts, Success of UN Assistance Mission in Iraq Ahead of 'Honourable and Dignified' Closure amid Complex Regional Challenges
description: The United Nations mission in Iraq will close its doors this month after more than two decades, its senior leader told the Security Council today, as delegates hailed its work and orderly exit amid complex regional conditions.
